    <thetext>Description of problem:

Under Fedora, &apos;ninja&apos; is shipped as &apos;ninja-build&apos; and since the completion
script invoke &apos;ninja&apos;, it surely doesn&apos;t work.

I also think that the &apos;/usr/share/bash/completions/ninja-bash-completion&apos; is not
named correctly, it should be simply &apos;ninja-build&apos;.

Additional info:

Might be related: https://lists.fedoraproject.org/pipermail/scm-commits/Week-of-Mon-20150202/1506322.html

If a fix is applied, we have to consider the following ticket about renaming &apos;ninja-build&apos; for &apos;ninja&apos;: https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1166135</thetext>
